Type of Intervention:
Cash transfer + in-kind (or other) - 1. Water supply: 4,082 households (20,000people) get water delivered over 5 months, which means until the major rainy seasonofMeherRainssetsin;
2. Livestock:2,550 households(12,495people) will receive fodder for their animals (2,883 cattle and 5,667 small ruminants);
3. Cash for Work: 7,500 households (36,750people)take part in the Cash for Work measures for the construction of rain water collection tanks and road rehabilitation;
4. Agriculture: 7,732 households (37,887 people) will receive drought-resistant and yielding seed;
5. Poultry Production:1,500 women-headed households (7,350 people) receive hens which are adapted to the local breeds for egg production;
6. Construction of drinking water Systems: 2,806 households (13,750 people) have access to drinking water through 6 newly drilled shallowwells, 24 new dug wells and 19 rehabilitated dug wells.
